Program: The Why Factor
Title: Safe Space
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03wd1vd
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 6 Jun 2016
The ideal university experience is expected to train the minds of students by exposing them to new ideas and challenging their assumptions. Why then, in the English speaking west at least, are some students rebelling against this principle by insisting there are some ideas which are so abhorrent they should not be heard? To them a university should be a safe space. In this edition of the Why Factor, Mike Williams tries to discover where the balance lies between freedom of speech and protection from offence and asks what exactly is a safe space? Producer: Sandra Kanthal Image: Students sharing space on campus (Credit: Rawpixel/ Shutterstock) Show less